deck: The first headquarters of the Justice League Europe.
description:
Origin

The Justice League Embassy in Paris is the first headquarters of the Justice League Europe. Before it was even set up a Nazi was murdered in the front hall and it was stormed by a mind controlled Paris mob.

Members

This is a list of members, employees and or families that used the location as a headquarters or took up residence in the Embassy itself.

  • Animal Man
  • Captain Atom
  • Catherine Cobert (Paris Embassy Chief)
  • Elongated Man
  • Flash: Wally West
  • Metamorpho
  • Power Girl
  • Rocket Red #4
  • Sub Dibney (Wife of Elongated Man and employee manning the monitor)
  • Wonder Woman

deck: The florist shop owned by Dinah Lance in Seattle.

Upon moving to Seattle, Dinah Lance opened her florist shop, Sherwood Florist. Dinah and Oliver Queen lived above the shop. Dinah and Ollie also frequently use the delivery van to get around the city while crimefighting.

Sherwood Florist is destroyed when Dinah is helping Jack Lynch, who is on the run.

Past workers include: Dinah Lance, Oliver Queen, Marianne, Colin.
